# Commit, Code, and Test Style Guide

- Use the conventional commit message format for all commits.
- Always write in English and include comments in code, tests, and commit messages.
- Prefer core and standard libraries when possible.
- Use idiomatic patterns and best practices for the language in use.
- For tests, unite related tests in a suite when possible.
